I put it on pan-fried ciabatta buns using walnut oil, and the sauce is Noh Hawaiian BBQ, the glaze was the leavings from the pre-roast pan searing, and the leftover marinade mixed with 2 Tbsp of apricot jam, a splash of extra-virgin olive oil, cooked in a saucepan for about 10 min. Before you put the meat to marinate for about 1-2 days take a knife and cut slits in the meat, peal and crush a few garlic cloves, and stuff the holes. time is 10 minutes at 400F per side per pound, alternating, so for 2 pounds, you turn it 4 times. plus 10 minutes to glaze it, I nigger-rigged an air fryer using my dutch oven and some balls of aluminum foil, try this at home kids.
